at endpoints with curl or other client programs; (2) it pushes you in a HAT=
EOAS direction. For example, if I=92m processing a conditional PUT, and I w=
ant to return a 412 (Precondition Failed), it leads me to put *something* i=
n the response body, because I want to show that programmer something in th=
e browser. Probably I would put the current version of the resource with an=
other &lt;form&gt; for editing it.
&gt;  
&gt; But now, if I also add program-friendly =
representations for the resources (Atom, JSON, etc.), then I=92ve now set u=
p a programmatic client with enough context to continue along with whatever=
