he server. i.e. my client doesn=92t have to have logic like =93if I get a 4=
12, do another GET, then try to do your PUT again=94. Instead, it can say =
=93ah, I got a 412 in response to my PUT; does the representation I got bac=
k match my desired state or not?=94 followed either by moving onto the next=
 goal or doing a new PUT, as desired.
